"use strict";(self.webpackChunk_N_E=self.webpackChunk_N_E||[]).push([[770],{7770:function(e,t,o){o.r(t),o.d(t,{GOLD_COAT:function(){return a}});let a={id:"goldCoat",title:"The Gold Coat Pirate",shortDescription:"A pirate who dreams of becoming royalty.",skillGrid:{exploration:["star","open","open","open","star","blocked","blocked"],brawn:["star","open","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked","blocked"],hunting:["star","open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked"],aim:["open","open","star","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"],swagger:["star","star","open","open","star","star","blocked"],navigation:["star","open","open","star","blocked","blocked","blocked"]},constellation:o(9774).Ir,storyBlanks:[{number:1,prompt:"An important position of power",type:"text"},{number:2,prompt:"A fancy-sounding adjective",type:"text"},{number:3,prompt:"A rare and expensive material",type:"text"},{number:4,prompt:"A name for a snooty servant",type:"text"},{number:5,prompt:"The pirate name of another player",type:"player_name"}],backstory:"I was born to rule! Unfortunately, I was born to a pair of fishmongers who had about as much power as a damp match. But I always knew I was meant for greater things. As a child, I would wrap meself in old fishin' nets and pretend they were royal robes. I'd make the neighborhood cats kneel before me. I once demanded a seagull address me as Your {2} Majesty. It did not.\n\nWhen I came of age, I decided the fastest way to power was through piracy. Accumulate enough treasure, and surely I could buy my way into the ranks of the royals! So I signed on with a pirate crew, wearing a coat I'd gilded with what little gold I had. The other pirates laughed at my gold coat, but they won't be laughin' when I'm their {1}. I've already begun training {4}, a member of the crew, to be my personal servant when the time comes. They don't know it yet, of course. I need {5} on my side too, as they seem to have some influence around here. One day, they will all bow before me.",events:[{narrative:"I found a chest of {3} buried on that last island. This is exactly the kind of material I need to upgrade my coat! When the crew saw me wearin' it, decked out in my finest, even {5} had to admit I looked positively {2}.",effect:"Treasure +1. Infamy +1."},{narrative:"I convinced {4} to polish my boots and bring me breakfast in bed. They grumbled about it, but I assured them that when I am {1}, they will be richly rewarded for their loyalty. I even let them try on my coat for a moment. They looked terrible in it, of course.",effect:"Re-roll +1. Discontent -1."},{narrative:"A royal merchant vessel surrendered to us today, and among the plunder was a crown! Well, more of a tiara, really. But it's made of real {3} and it fits me perfectly. I wore it all day. Nobody said anything, but I could tell they were impressed.",effect:"Retrieve card 44 Minor Crown from the story deck."},{narrative:"I've been studying royal etiquette from a book I found in the captain's quarters. Did you know that a proper {1} never scratches themselves in public? I've been practicin' not scratchin' for three whole days now. It is torture, but this is the kind of sacrifice a ruler must make.",effect:"Swagger +1. Gain 1 skill of your choice."},{narrative:"{5} and I had a long talk about leadership tonight. I told them about my plans to become {1}, and they actually seemed supportive! Either that or they were just humoring me to make me shut up. Either way, I feel validated.",effect:"Crew +2. Infamy +1."}],endings:{bad:{threshold:"≤3",text:"Your dreams of royalty never quite materialize. After your pirating days, you try to buy a title from a shady noble, but the title turns out to be fake — you are now the {1} of an island that doesn't exist. {4} abandons you, tired of polishing boots for no pay. {5} won't return your letters. You spend your remaining gold on a {2} mansion that turns out to be infested with rats. Your gold coat tarnishes to a dull green. You sit on a moth-eaten throne made of driftwood, ruling over a kingdom of cobwebs and regret. The only subject who still acknowledges you is a stray cat who sits on your lap, but only because you smell like fish."},good:{threshold:"4",text:"You may not become a true royal, but with the treasure you've accumulated, you come close enough. You purchase a large estate and hire {4} as your actual butler, paying them handsomely. You commission a {2} portrait of yourself in your gold coat and hang it above the fireplace. You throw lavish parties where you insist everyone address you as Your {2} Excellency. {5} attends once and calls it the most ridiculous and most fun evening they've ever had. You may be a commoner playing pretend, but you play pretend better than anyone, and you live a life of comfort and absurd luxury."},legendary:{threshold:"5",text:"Against all odds, your relentless pursuit of power actually pays off. Using the treasures, connections, and reputation you've built, you navigate the complex world of royal politics and are appointed {1} of a small but prosperous coastal territory. Your first act is to commission a new coat made entirely of {3}. Your second act is to officially appoint {4} as your Grand Vizier, a title they accept with tears of confused joy. {5} becomes your Royal Advisor, and together you govern with a combination of pirate pragmatism and royal ambition. Your territory becomes known for its fairness, its absurdly lavish parties, and the solid gold statue of yourself in the town square. The neighboring royals think you're ridiculous, but your people love you, and that is all that matters."}}}}}]);